<HEADLINE> Germany Extends Ban on British Beef Imports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Germany has reiterated its strong
stance on the "mad cow" issue today by extending indefinitely a
total ban against imports of beef and beef products from Britain
and Switzerland.
</P>
<P>
For fear of the possible human version of "mad cow" disease,
the German government adopted an emergency measure on March 28 to
ban Britain's beef exports.
</P>
<P>
The Agriculture Ministry said in a statement today that Germany
had decided that the measure which will be expired on September 29
will be ratified by the Bundesrat, the upper house of parliament,
to be an indefinite one.
</P>
<P>
The European Union (EU) agreed last month to ease its overall
ban against British beef on condition that London carrys out a
program to eradicate "mad cow" disease, formally known as bovine
spongiform encephalopathy (BSE).
</P>
<P>
However, five of the EU's 15 member nations, including Germany,
the main force against lifting the ban, voted against the decision
and refused to carry it out.
</P>
<P>
A panel of experts from the European Commission, or the EU's
executive arm, and EU member states are to visit Britain on July
22 to inspect implementation of Britain's eradication program.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
