<HEADLINE> Arrests Made in Sicily on Mafia Charges </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, July 10 (Xinhua) -- The Sicilian police said today they
had arrested 41 suspects on Mafia charges in their latest
operation against a ring allegedly responsible for numerous
murders, kidnapings and robberies and drug trafficking.
</P>
<P>
The operation was aided by information offered by two Mafia
turncoats, police said.
</P>
<P>
The arrested were suspected of belonging to an extortion clan
headed by Raffaele Ganci, the Mafia boss who controlled the
Sicilian capital of Palermo.
</P>
<P>
Ganci is now in custody accused of links to the killing of
anti-Mafia Judge Giovanni Falcone in 1992.
</P>
<P>
On Tuesday, a total of 156 Mafia suspects were arrested in
northern and central Italy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
