<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sichuan Quanxing Enters CSA Cup Top Eight </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, Sichuan Province, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Sichuan Quanxing
repeated its Sunday's 3-2 win over the Chinese Army in the second
leg competition at the second round of Chinese Soccer Association
Cup here on Wednesday, advancing to the quarter-finals with an
aggregate 6-4 victory.
</P>
<P>
Quanxing, a fifth placer in the national league which laid off
after its first round robin competition, placed emphasis on
defence with a first leg win in hands while the Chinese Army also
played a very cautious game.
</P>
<P>
The deadlock was not broken until the 42nd minute when Zou
Yougen opened the scoring for Quanxing with a header.
</P>
<P>
Brazil's Andre added the second one minute later after a
brilliant combination with teammate Penxiaofang to give Quanxing a
2-0 lead.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Army struggled to score its first goal by Zhao
Jialin just before the break.
</P>
<P>
National player Hao Haidong managed to equal the score on an
error of Quanxing only seconds into the second half.
</P>
<P>
Quanxing's win came in the 65th minute when another Brasilian
Marmelo headed home a cross from his teammate.
</P>
<P>
The referee showed a total of four red cards and nine yellow
cards throughout the match, which was interrupted for about 10
minutes by the rows in field between the two sides.
</P>
<P>
In the day's other matches, Guangzhou Songri beat Qianwei
Huandao 2-0, Guangdong Hongyuan ousted Qingdao Hainiu 5-2, Beijing
Guo'an routed Shanghai Yuyuan 3-2, Jinan Taishan outplayed
Guangzhou Apollo 1-0, Shanghai Shenhua nipped Hubei Meierya 3-1,
Dalian Wanda edged Tianjin Samsung 2-1 and Shanghai Pudong tied
Liaoning Hangxing 2-2.
</P>
<P>
The other seven aggregate winners who will compete in Sunday's
first leg of quarter-finals are Songri, Hongyuan, Guo'an, Taishan,
Shenhua, Wanda and Pudong. 
</P>
</TEXT>
