<HEADLINE> Renault, Peugeot to Launch New Motor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 10 (Xinhua) -- The two major French auto producers
of Renault and PSA Peugeot Citroen today presented a new V6 motor
they jointly made to replace an old V6 launched 20 years ago.
</P>
<P>
The two companies, and the Swedish auto producer the Volvo,
began to jointly make V6 motor in 1974, which was also called RPV
to mark cooperations between the three companies.
</P>
<P>
The new V6 motor, called ES/L will have six cylinders in V form
with 60 degree angles, which will be fixed on vehicles from both
companies to be sold from autumn this year, said company sources.
</P>
