<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Report: Children's Mortality in South Asia Falls </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Children's mortality in South Asia
has fallen greatly over the past three decades, according to a
report by the United Nations International Children's Emergency
Fund (UNICEF).
</P>
<P>
The report on the conditions of children worldwide, which was
released here by the Cairo-based Afro-Asian People's Solidarity
Organization (AAPSO), said that one out of every eight children
under the age of five dies in South Asia.
</P>
<P>
In 1960, one out of every four children under five died, the
report said. The figures of the report were carried by Egypt's
Middle East News Agency today.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, more and more girls in South Asia are
receiving elementary education, but boys receiving education still
largely outnumber girls who receive education. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
