<HEADLINE> Indonesia to Build Waste Processing Plants </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 11 (Xinhua) -- The Indonesian government will
grant low-interest loans and facilities for industries, which plan
to build their liquid processing plants, to import equipment, an
official said here today.
</P>
<P>
These industries will be granted loans payable in 25 to 30
years and will be allowed to import equipment subject to tax
concessions and free import duties, deputy chairman of the Agency
for Control of Environment Impact Sukardi told a seminar on the
biotechnological processing of solid and liquid wastes.
</P>
<P>
Sukardi said many industries across the country have availed of
these facilities to set up their liquid waste processing plants.
</P>
<P>
He said the government had decided to extend these facilities
to boost efforts to protect the environment and encourage the
private sector to prepare for global competition.
</P>
<P>
The industries need to incorporate the environment factor in
their business operations to ensure the sustainability of natural
resources and the competitiveness of their products. 
</P>
