<HEADLINE> SAARC, EU to Promote Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, July 11 (Xinhua) -- The South Asian Association for
Regional Cooperation (SAARC) and the European Union (EU) have set
up a mechanism for promoting mutual cooperation, the SAARC
secretariat here said today.
</P>
<P>
A memorandum of understanding (MOU) on administrative
cooperation between the EU and SAARC, signed Wednesday by SAARC
secretary-general Naeem U. Hasan during his visit to the EU
headquarters in Brussels, was the first step of such a mechanism,
according to a SAARC press release.
</P>
<P>
The MOU mainly focused on exchange of information,
institutional support and training, and technical assistance, it
said.
</P>
<P>
Bilateral cooperation between the EU and all of the SAARC
member countries has been existing for a long time, but a strong
willingness to improve and strengthen relations between the SAARC
and EU emerged on both sides only in recent years, according to
the release.
</P>
<P>
SAARC, formed in 1985, groups Bangladesh, India, Nepal,
Pakistan, Sri Lanka, the Maldives and Bhutan.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
