<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, July 11 (Xinhua) -- Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak
said today that a military training agreement signed between
Turkey and Israel is aimed at training and does not aim to form a
military "pact" in this region.
</P>
<P>
Mubarak, who arrived here this morning for a one-day working
visit to Turkey, made the remarks at a joint press conference
given by him and his Turkish counterpart Suleyman Demirel.
</P>
<P>
The Egyptian president said that he and Demirel held talks on
bilateral relations as well as regional and international issues.
</P>
<P>
