<HEADLINE> EU, SAARC Sign Administrative Cooperation Memorandum </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, July 11 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) and the
South Asian Association for Regional Cooperation (SAARC) have
decided to go on with administration cooperation.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman of the European Commission (EC), the executive arm
of the EU, announced today that a memorandum of understanding in
this regard was signed here yesterday.
</P>
<P>
The document, the spokesman said, calls for exchanges of
information, institutional support and training, and technical
assistance.
</P>
<P>
"This is a first step in setting up a mechanism for promoting
cooperation between the two organizations," he noted, adding that
the two sides have a strong willingness to improve and enlarge
their relations.
</P>
<P>
The SAARC is a regional body founded in 1985 which groups
Bangladesh, Bhutan, India, the Maldives, Nepal, Pakistan and Sri
Lanka.
</P>
<P>
Political dialogue between the EU and SAARC was officially
opened in September 1994, when the foreign ministers of the
countries occupying EU's rotating presidency met in New York with
the Bangladesh foreign minister, who represented at that time the
SAARC chairmanship.  
</P>
</TEXT>
