<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran Faces Population Explosion (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Some political analysts noted that it is too late for the
Islamic regime to realize the importance of birth control across
the country, because the population is now too large to control.
</P>
<P>
The problem of the swelling population has seriously affected
the society in various fields ranging from economy, employment,
education to welfare and medical care.
</P>
<P>
Health Minister Marandi told Xinhua, "We are developing country
and we should be able to develop our country faster than the
developed countries. We need to have population under control."
</P>
<P>
He said that Iran used to have a very high population growth
rate of 3.9 percent. It started family planning in 1989. "We have
been able to bring the growth rate from 3.9 percent to 1.56
percent in the past six or seven years."
</P>
<P>
Judging from the past success, the Iranian minister was
optimistic about the family planning policy in his country,
saying that he had some doubts about the doubling of the
population in the next 25 years.
</P>
<P>
He argued, "If things go well it should not double before 40
years. We are gradually improving our situation."
</P>
<P>
Marandi said that the Iranian government will continue to
implement the family policy. "Our hope is that people would
decide on two children."
</P>
<P>
However, he added, "We have not restricted below the line. We
even allow three children for each family."
</P>
<P>
"If a family has more than three children, they will lose some
of their benefits such as subsidy on their health insurance, and
subsidies that they are getting for other things would be taken
away from them," he said.
</P>
<P>
So, he continued, three children is still acceptable. "But we
are hoping that they would have two."
</P>
<P>
"If they would prefer one for each family, we would like that
also. And if they would decide not to have any children at all, we
don't mind that either. We are after a lower population growth for
the entire country," he stressed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
