<HEADLINE> American Investors Show Interest in Investing in Chongqing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, July 11 (Xinhua) -- The United States plans to
invest in energy development and environmental protection in
Chongqing, the largest city in Southwest China.
</P>
<P>
According to Richard Ellings, executive director of the
National Bureau of Asian Research of the United States, who is
visiting the city, a United States-Chongqing energy and
environment technology cooperative project will be formed in
Seattle.
</P>
<P>
He said he hopes the project will encourage major companies in
the United States to invest in Chongqing's energy development, and
also energy-saving and environmental protection technology.
</P>
<P>
So far, six American companies -- AMECO, TEXICO, UNOCAL,
ENTERGY and OWEN COLLINGS -- have joined the project.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Delin, secretary of the Chongqing Committee of the
Communist Party of China, said that the cooperative project will
help boost Chongqing's economy and help advance its opening to the
outside world. 
</P>
</TEXT>
