<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Schedules Eighth Bond Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The bonds will be issued in three denominations: 100 yuan,
1,000 yuan and 5,000 yuan. Principal and interest, which will be
calculated starting the first day of the bond issue, will be
repayable after the bonds mature on August 6, 1999.
</P>
<P>
The bonds can be listed and traded on the secondary market
immediately after issuance, the announcement said.
</P>
<P>
The bonds first will be underwritten, through open bidding, by
primary dealers and other securities institutions before they are
offered to the public.
</P>
<P>
This year, China has floated seven groups of treasury bonds
valued at more than 112 billion yuan in aggregate. The country's
treasury bond issuance this year has been budgeted at 195.257
billion yuan, up from more than 152 billion yuan in 1995. 
</P>
</TEXT>
