<HEADLINE> Top Seed Black Advances in Hall of Fame Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Top seed Byron Black of
Zimbabwe held off South African qualifier Robbie Koenig to enter
the quarter-finals of the 230,000 U.S. dollars Hall of Fame tennis
tournament in Newport, Rhode Island, on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Black, ranked 29th in the world, needed one hour, 42 minutes
to beat Koenig 6-3, 5-7, 6-2.
</P>
<P>
But seeds continued to fall at the only grass court tournament
on the ATP Tour in the United States.
</P>
<P>
A pair of Australians, fourth seed Sandon Stolle and fifth
seed Patrick Rafter, and eighth seed Mark Knowles of the Bahamas
were second-round upset victims.
</P>
<P>
South African Marcos Ondruska took advantage of nine double
faults to oust Stolle 6-2, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
Canadian Daniel Nestor knocked out Rafter 7-5, 3-6, 7-6 (10-8)
while Leander Paes of India needed almost three hours to rally to
beat Knowles 6-7 (3-7), 7-6 (7-5), 7-5. 
</P>
</TEXT>
