<HEADLINE> Air China Gets Big Bank Loans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 11 (Xinhua) -- Air China, the country's national
flag carrier, will receive 400 million yuan (about 47.6 million US
dollars) in working capital loans from the Bank of China (BOC),
according to an agreement the two sides signed here today.
</P>
<P>
As the largest aviation firm in China, Air China currently has
a fleet of 62 aircraft, including Boeing-747s and Boeing-767s. It
flies 116 international and domestic air routes and boasts a
flying safety record of 40 years.
</P>
<P>
The national flag carrier registered a sales revenue of 10.87
billion yuan and a profit of 460 million yuan in 1995.
</P>
<P>
The BOC, one of China's four largest banks, will gradually pump
several billion yuan into key sectors, according to a bank
official. 
</P>
</TEXT>
