<HEADLINE> Shanghai Colleges to Jointly Train Medicine Students </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 11 (Xinhua) -- A comprehensive university and a
medical science college in Shanghai have jointed hands in a
two-way education program to train senior medical personnel.
</P>
<P>
Fudan University and the Shanghai No.2 Medical Science
University have signed an agreement to jointly train seven-year
medical students in basic science courses and social science
theories.
</P>
<P>
Students majoring in clinical medicine and stomatology at the
Shanghai No.2 Medical Science University will study basic courses
of liberal arts and sciences in the first academic year, and
courses of life sciences and new frontier medical sciences, in the
sixth year at Fudan University.
</P>
<P>
Medical students at Fudan will receive all medicine courses in
the third, fourth and fifth years, and some courses in the second
and sixth years, at the No.2 Medical Science University.
</P>
<P>
The two schools have co-operated to train students of medical
majors since 1988. They will jointly train masters and doctors of
medical sciences in future.
</P>
<P>
In addition to personnel training, the two schools have also
established a genetics and medical science research
center. 
</P>
</TEXT>
