<DOCNO> XIE19960711.0069 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-07-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World Bank Funds Health Project in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, July 11 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank today announced a
350 million US dollar reproductive and child health project in
India, the Press Trust of India said.
</P>
<P>
The project will support the family welfare program in India
and focus on increasing the availability of reproductive choices
and improving the heath of children in the country.
</P>
<P>
A press release issued by the bank in Washington said that the
project would eventually contribute to the stabilization of
population growth.
</P>
<P>
The Indian project is one of several the bank is taking up in
accordance with the agenda set by the Cairo conference on
population and development in September, 1994.  
</P>
