<HEADLINE> EU Finances Reconstruction Projects in ACP Countries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, July 11 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) today
decided to finance 21 reconstruction projects in eight African,
Caribbean and Pacific (ACP) countries.
</P>
<P>
Recipients of the aid, approved by the European Commission
(EC), the executive arm of the EU, Angola, Eritrea, Ethiopia,
Haiti, Mozambique, Rwanda, Somalia and Zaire.
</P>
<P>
The countries, mainly in Africa, were affected by serious civil
disturbances or natural disasters.
</P>
<P>
The total amount of the projects is estimated to be 11.1
million ECUs, or 14.4 million U.S. dollars. Rwanda, Mozambique,
Zaire and Haiti are to benefit the most.
</P>
<P>
The move is part of the EC's aid package extended to ACP
countries to contribute to their political and social stability.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1995, 107 projects in ACP countries had been
financed, valued at 63.6 million ECUs, or 82.7 million dollars.
</P>
