<HEADLINE> Hong Kong to Host Women's World Cup Table Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 11 (Xinhua/OANA) -- The first women's World Cup
</P>
<P>
table tennis Tournament will be held in September at Elizabeth
Stadium of Hong Kong, it was announced here today.
</P>
<P>
Sixteen of the world's top female table tennis players will
join the tournament to compete for the sport's highest ever prize
of 75,000 US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The event is presented by sports cable network ESPN, organized
by the Hong Kong Table Tennis Association (HKTTA), and has the
official sanction of the International Table Tennis Federation
(ITTF).
</P>
<P>
Chairman of HKTTA Tony Yue said: "As a matter of fact, the
first Men's World Cup was also held in Hong Kong back in 1980.
HKTTA enjoys the distinguished honor of being the first host
organizer of both events."
</P>
<P>
He said that the 16 women players will be the champions of
Asia, South America, North America, Australia and Europe; six
top-ranked players; three wildcard players and one player from the
organizing unit.
</P>
<P>
He said that ITTF pays high regards to this tournament, its
current President Xu Yinsheng and four vice-presidents will come
to Hong Kong to attend the match. 
</P>
