<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Stronger </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, July 11 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar was firmer
against the US dollar today.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar ended at 79.91 US cents from 79.63 US
cents on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Local traders expected the Australian dollar to climb higher
during trading in overseas market tonight. Some said that if the
currency broke through the 80 US cent barrier tonight, it might
rise to 80.15-80.20 US cents.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar was boosted by expectations of higher
demand for commodities as the world economy picked up speed. As a
major commodities exporter in the world, Australia has always seen
the movement of its currency linked to commodity prices.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar ended at 88.18 yen against the Japanese
yen from 87.76 yen yesterday. It was traded at 88 yen in the
European market, the highest level since November 1992.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar strengthened to 1.2196 marks against the
German mark from 1.2147 marks on Wednesday.  
</P>
