<HEADLINE> 8 Rebels Killed, 20 Injured in Easter Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, July 11 (Xinhua) -- At least 8 rebels were killed and
20 others injured in fighting between government troops and the
Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE) rebels in Eastern province
of Sri Lanka today.
</P>
<P>
According to a military spokesman here, the government troops
Wednesday commenced an operation code named "Seda Pahara" (be
struck by lightning) in Batticaloa district in order to destroy
the LTTE rebel bases in the area.
</P>
<P>
The government troops this morning confronted two LTTE rebel
groups, killing at least 8 rebels and wounding over 20 others.
</P>
<P>
The government troops did not suffer any casualties during the
confrontation, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE has been fighting against the government for a
separate Tamil state in the north and east of the country since
1983.  
</P>
