<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. Dream Team Downs Chinese Olympians by 61 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHOENIX, July 10 (Xinhua/OANA) -- The U.S. Dream Team proved
that it is getting better and better since their gathering a
couple of weeks ago as the Olympic favorite trounced the Chinese
Team 119-58 in a warm-up game here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Dunkings, steals and fast breaks, the Dream Team showed a real
NBA basketball before a crowd of 20,000-seat fans at American West
Arena, with Reggie Miller leading the hosts with 16 points.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. team, which got a narrow win over the American
under-22 Selected Team by only six points and big victory over
Brazil by 41 points last sunday, never trailed during the game
after Charles Barkley, who just became free agent from the Phoenix
Suns, scored the first points on his two free throws and first six
in the second half.
</P>
<P>
"We won the game thanks to our good and aggressive defense,
which made things happen," said Lenny Wilkens, coach of the Dream
Team.
</P>
<P>
The Americans built a 13-3 lead only less two minutes into the
game and scored 62 points in the first half, enough for winning
the exhibition, while China got 38 points.
</P>
<P>
The second half was more worse for the visitors, who will play
the Dream Team in the group A during the Olympic Games opening on
July 19, when the U.S. counterparts played almost without
challenge by 13 of 22 slam dunkings and 10 of 21 steals.
</P>
<P>
"I didn't expect we could lost more than 60 points. I thought
40 or 50 was possible," the Chinese Team coach Gong Luming said.
</P>
<P>
"We played well in the first half, compared to the second half
where We were under our normal level," he added.
</P>
<P>
China scored all eight three-pointers in the first half with
two each by Zheng Wu and Hu Weidong.
</P>
<P>
"Too many turnovers and poor reboundings were the main reason
to be beaten by such a big margin. They played very good fast
break which made us more difficult to match up," the Chinese Team
captain Wu Qinglong said.
</P>
<P>
China committed 27 tourovers, 16 in the first half, and was
outrebouned by the Dream Team 20-42.
</P>
<P>
"We didn't care what points we should win over China before the
game," Shaquille O'neal said, "We just scored and played the game,
do our best."
</P>
<P>
Grant Hill scored 14 points for the Dream Team, and Scottie
Pippen added 12 and Charles Barkley 11.
</P>
<P>
Wang Zhizhi, 19-year-old center, led the Chinese Team with 12
points from his 23 minutes play. He was followed by Zheng Wu with
10 and Hu Weidong eight.
</P>
<P>
The Dream Team will play against Australia in Salt Lake City on
Friday, the fourth of its five warm-up games for the Olympics
which opens July 19. 
</P>
</TEXT>
