<HEADLINE> Former Israeli Minister Accuses Netanyahu of Adopting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, July 11 (Xinhua) -- Former Israeli Minister of Science
and Education Sholamit Aloni has condemned what she called
arrogant colonial policies adopted by Israeli Prime Minister
Benjamin Netanyahu.
</P>
<P>
In a telephone interview with Egypt's English-language
newspaper Al-Ahram Weekly, Aloni warned that the colonial policies
are a threat to the existence of the state of Israel.
</P>
<P>
"Israel is the only country left in the world that insists on
remaining a colonial state -- one that has usurped the land and
rights of another people and continues to subject them to
oppression, " said Aloni, who was also the former leader of the
Meretz Party.
</P>
<P>
In the interview carried by the paper published today, she said
the colonial policies must end, otherwise Netanyahu will isolate
Israel once again within the international community and alienate
it from the Arab world.
</P>
<P>
Aloni has pressed upon Netanyahu with a need for Israel to
return the Golan Heights to Syria.
</P>
<P>
"The quicker we give the Golan Heights back to Syria, the
sooner our political and moral losses in Israel will be
alleviated," said the minister in the former Israeli government
led by Shimon Peres, Netanyahu's predecessor.
</P>
<P>
"Netanyahu has to choose between his arrogance and building
healthy relations with the Arabs -- and the first step toward this
is to restore their usurped rights to them," she said.
</P>
<P>
She urged U.S. President Bill Clinton to use strong persuasive
measures on Netanyahu and encourage him to continue the peace
process on the basis of the "land-for-peace" formula.
</P>
<P>
"The only remaining hope is that world powers will bring
pressure to bear on Netanyahu and that he will feel the sting of
economic pressures," she said. 
</P>
