<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 11 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Li Lanqing
said here today that China is willing to further strengthen mutual
trade cooperation with Japan, China's largest trade partner.
</P>
<P>
Li said that Sino-Japanese trade cooperation is beneficial to
the region's economic development, as well as to the rest of the
world.
</P>
<P>
Li made the remark in Beijing this morning while meeting with
Deputy Vice-Director General of Foreign Affairs Ogura Kazuo of the
Japanese Foreign Ministry, who is here to report on the G-7 summit
in Lyon, France.
</P>
