<HEADLINE> Iranian President: No Worry over US Sanctions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, July 11 (Xinhua) -- Iranian President Akbar Hashemi
Rafsanjani said here today that Iran should not have the
slightest worry over the U.S. sanctions on the country because
these sanctions will prove to be a total failure.
</P>
<P>
The 61-year-old president declared that Iran is not in need
of the United States and is not dependent on America.
Therefore, the nation need not to be concerned with the
sanctions.
</P>
<P>
Rafsanjani made the statement while addressing telecommunications
ministers and representatives from 40 member states of the
Organization of the Islamic Conference (OIC) at the inaugural
ceremony of a major center for long distance and international
telecommunications.
</P>
<P>
The United States imposed economic sanctions on the Islamic
Republic since June 1995, banning all U.S. companies from trading
and investing in Iran, particularly in oil and gas sector.
</P>
<P>
Now, Washington is going to impose secondary sanctions against
any foreign companies investing 40 million U.S. dollars or more
in Iranian oil and gas industries in a single year.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian authorities criticized the United States for
violation of free trade under the framework of the international
laws and regulations.
</P>
<P>
Rafsanjani stressed that the appropriate road to attain power
and independence should be taken through construction and Iran
has gone through a major part of this path.
</P>
<P>
"If countries want to attain their legitimate rights and
not to bow to enemies, they should follow the path of
construction," he added.
</P>
<P>
He said that as the zealous Iranian specialists are working
relentlessly and with remarkable determination and have succeeded
in meeting all the needs of the nation, the U.S. can do nothing.
</P>
