<HEADLINE> Telecom Business Deregulation Called For </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, July 11 (Xinhua) -- The head of Japan's Economic
Planning Agency (EPA) has called for implementing a drastic
deregulation of the nation's telecommunications industry where
would-be entrants are currently placed under severe official
curbs, Kyodo News Service reported.
</P>
<P>
Japan should allow a greater number of other (telecom business)
carriers to enter or get out of the telecommunications sector,
said Shusei Tanaka, the agency's director general, at a breakfast
meeting with the leaders of the Federation of Economic
Organizations (Keidanren).
</P>
<P>
Tanaka said deregulation should be given priority as it would
lead to helping secure a self-sustained recovery of the economy.
</P>
<P>
Keidanren Chairman Shoichiro Toyoda agreed with Tanaka on the
need to avoid giving further strains to the nation's already
overburdened finances. 
</P>
