<HEADLINE> 9 Killed in Plane Crash in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, July 11 (Xinhua) -- Nine people, including three
crew members, were killed when a civilian plane crashed in
Himachal Pradesh, North India, this morning, the Press Trust of
India (PTI) reported.
</P>
<P>
The plane, which was flying from Shimla to Kulu, was first
reported missing, but later on a villager informed police about
its wreckage at a place about 22 kilometers northeast of Kulu.
</P>
