<HEADLINE> India's Exports to ASEAN Grow Fast: Report </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, July 11 (Xinhua) -- India's exports to the countries
of the Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) are growing
fast, with those to Vietnam expanding at the fastest rate, the
Times of India reported today.
</P>
<P>
India's overall trade with the six ASEAN members rose to 9,137
crore rupees (2.61 billion US dollars) in the fiscal year of
1995-96, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Singapore, accounting for one-third of India's total exports to
the region in the fiscal year, was India's largest ASEAN market,
followed by Indonesia and Thailand.
</P>
<P>
The most rapid growth of India's exports to the region took
place in Vietnam, which recorded a dramatic increase of 171
percent from the previous fiscal year, with pharmaceuticals
topping the export list.  
</P>
</TEXT>
