<HEADLINE> Iran: Egypt Puts Pre-condition on Resuming </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, July 11 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Foreign Minister Ali Akbar
Velayati has said that Cairo has put pre-conditions for
normalization of ties with Tehran, local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
Velayati's statement was carried on the front page of the
English-language daily Iran News. However, the report gave no
details about the pre-conditions for resumption of the diplomatic
relations between the two countries, which was broken after the
signing of the Camp David Accord in 1979.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian government has expressed regret over the statement
by Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak, who rejected Syrian mediation
between Tehran and Cairo, on grounds that Tehran is still trying
to undermine the Egyptian government.
</P>
<P>
Mahmoud Mohammadi, spokesman for the Iranian Foreign Ministry,
claimed that "Iran will only resume diplomatic ties with Egypt if
it distances itself from the Zionist regime."
</P>
<P>
The Iranian spokesman termed the Egyptian official approach on
the Syrian diplomacy as a "regrettable effort," which is aimed at
crippling the Syrian trouble-shooting shuttle diplomacy.
</P>
<P>
Appreciating the Syrian efforts, he said that Iran has always
been on the Syria's side from the very onset after the Islamic
revolution and will continue to stand by the people and
government of Syria, particularly in their quest to liberate
their occupied lands. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
