<HEADLINE> Mubarak Visits Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, July 11 (Xinhua) -- Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak
arrived here this morning for a one-day working visit to Turkey
at the invitation of his Turkish counterpart Suleyman Demirel.
</P>
<P>
Demirel met Mubarak at the airport and the two presidents
flew to the presidential palace in Ankara by helicopter.
</P>
<P>
Demirel will soon hold a welcoming ceremony for Mubarak in
the presidential palace.
</P>
<P>
Mubarak is paying the working visit for a day of fence mending
with Turkey.
</P>
<P>
The relations between Turkey and Egypt suffered when Egyptian
officials blasted Ankara's military accord with Israel and
actively campaigned against it in the Arab world.
</P>
<P>
The agreement allows the Israeli jets to train in Turkey.
</P>
<P>
Dismissing protests from the alarmed neighbors, Turkish
officials have defended the accord, saying it enables the
Turkish pilots to get electronic warfare training in Israel in
return for the favor granted to the Jewish state.
</P>
<P>
Egypt's suspicions center on fears that a new grouping is
emerging in the Middle East between Turkey, Jordan and Israel.
</P>
<P>
Egypt warned that the real intention of the Turco-Israeli
military accord was unclear.
</P>
<P>
In March, Demirel met with Mubarak in Aswan, Egypt, and
today's reciprocal visit is expected to focus on similar issues:
the Mideast Peace Process and Arab concerns over the
Turco-Israeli military agreement. 
</P>
</TEXT>
