<DATE_TIME> 1996-07-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Real Estate Prices in Hanoi Falling Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, July 11 (Xinhua)-- The real estate prices in Hanoi, the
capital of Vietnam, have been tumbling, especially since last
February, according to Vietnamese press.
</P>
<P>
The falling prices have focused on apartments and simple
one-storey government-owned houses which can be rebuilt into
bigger and higher houses.
</P>
<P>
With the land and house prices as a premium, many lucky people
became man of wealth overnight.
</P>
<P>
During the 1994-1995 period, an apartment on the third or
fourth floor in Li Duc street of Hanoi's Hai Ba Trung precinct was
sold at one tael of gold per square meter.
</P>
<P>
However, now they are sold at only about half that price, and
even so it's difficult to find buyers.
</P>
<P>
In Ngoc Khanh and Thanh Cong residences of the city, houses
have been sold at only 10 to 20 percent of the prices asked.
</P>
<P>
The glut of mini-hotels and restaurants has played a big part
in the slump. Most mini-hotels do not operate to their capacity
and many have closed.
</P>
<P>
Land and housing prices are coming down not only in Hanoi but
also in other cities of the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
