<HEADLINE> Transport Flourishing in South China City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, July 11 (Xinhua) -- The capital city of south China's
Hainan Province has seen the rapid growth of its transport sector
in the past five years, with 210 million passengers passing
through and a freight flow of 80 million tons.
</P>
<P>
At present, Haikou has 36,000 civil vehicles, 7.5 times that of
1987; and 170 commercial ships, ten times the number in 1987. The
ships have a total tonnage of 750,000 tons, 4.9 times more than
five years ago, and are able to accommodate 12,000 passengers, 1.7
times the 1990 total.
</P>
<P>
Haikou Airport has opened 51 domestic and four international
routes, and handles nearly 100 take-offs and landings daily.
</P>
<P>
Nine new berths were built at Haikou port over the past five
years, of which three have more than 10,000 DWT (dead weight
tonnage) each. Haikou port has 35 berths and handled more than 1.3
million tons of cargo last year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
