<HEADLINE> Villages To Have Phones In Tanzania Soon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, July 11 (Xinhua) -- The Tanzania Telecommunication
Company Limited has devised a program that will enable most of the
villages in semi-urban areas to be provided with telephones.
</P>
<P>
The Deputy Minister for Transport and Communications, Maua
Daftari, told the National Assembly in Dodoma, Central Tanzania on
Wednesday that the Program known as "Rural Automation Program"
would cost 207.34 million U.S. Dollars.
</P>
<P>
She said the program would enable rehabilitation and
installation of 47,664 phones in various villages and semi-urban
areas.
</P>
<P>
"Our aim is to improve telecommunication in villages and semi-urban
areasation so that they can cope with the current pace of technology," Daftari
said.
</P>
<P>
The Deputy minister said villages and semi-urban areas would be
provided with automatic digital telephones which will be connected by
digital radio system.
</P>
<P>
She said that areas with industries, tourism and big
farms would be given priority, adding that hospitals, courts, churches
and schools would also be considered.
</P>
<P>
According to the deputy minister, the Telecommunication
Restructuring Project (TRP), which is currently being undertaken
throughout the country, will enable various towns to be installed with
digital switches and radio links.
</P>
<P>
The installation will further improve telecommunications between
townships and villages, she said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
