<HEADLINE> Meningitis Under Control in Nigeria: Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, July 11 (Xinhua) -- Cerebro-spinal meningitis (CSM),
the dreaded disease that claimed the lives of thousands of people
in Nigeria early this year, has been brought under control.
</P>
<P>
No cases have been reported in the country since April, Health
Minister Ihechukwu Madubuike told an official of the World Health
Organization on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
However, the minister said, the current immunization exercise
will continue in order to forestall a recurrence.
</P>
<P>
On the reported outbreak of cholera in some parts of the
country, the minister said that measures had been adopted to
control the disease.
</P>
<P>
One of such measures is workshops currently taking place
nationwide to educate people on the effective treatment and
management of cholera.
</P>
<P>
Cases of cholera disease have been reported mainly in the
northeastern part of the country. According to a latest report,
450 people died of the disease in northeastern Borno state.
</P>
</TEXT>
