<HEADLINE> Zhejiang Strengthening Rural Ecology Protection </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, July 11 (Xinhua) -- East China's Zhejiang Province is
paying closer attention to rural environmental protection while
its economic development picks up pace.
</P>
<P>
By building trial ecological villages, pollution was
successfully controlled and resources more fully utilized in rural
areas, according to the local government.
</P>
<P>
The local government began the trials in the mid-1980s, with
rebuilding forests as the key.
</P>
<P>
Lingkun Island in Wenzhou city used to be a wasteland. It now
has more than 13 million trees on it.
</P>
<P>
In the process of protecting the ecological environment, the
local government has given its priority to the improvement of the
living environment. A number of fruit bases have been set up, and
rural energy and pesticide projects carried out.
</P>
<P>
Since 1990, efforts have been made in the control of fertilizer
pollution and pollution by township enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The province has 27 villages on the trial list, and according
to the plan, the number will increase to 100 by the end of 1997.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
