<HEADLINE> Kuwaiti Stocks Trading Up 200 Percent in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, July 11 (Xinhua) -- Trading volume and value at
the Kuwait Stock Exchange market increased by 259.1 percent and
226.3 percent respectively in 1995 over 1994 to reach nine
billion shares valued at 1.9 billion Kuwait dinars (6.27 Billion
U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The report issued by the Kuwait Stock Exchange said on
Wednesday that there were 104,218 contracts signed in 1995, and
that most active stocks in the country were those of the banking
sector, followed by the real estate and the investment sectors in
that order.
</P>
<P>
It said bartering activities during the year included 224.7
million shares traded at a value of 66.2 million Kuwait dinars
(218 million U.S. dollars). The banking sector ranked first in
the bartering activities.
</P>
<P>
Annual rotation, the report said, rose by 81.6 percent with
the banking sector topping the list of rotating sectors, which
netted 198.2 percent, followed by the real estate sector with
172.2 percent and the services sector with 108.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Kuwait shares dipped on busy profit taking in the
week to Wednesday, ending a month-long rally driven by
privatization and hopes of good bank results.
</P>
<P>
Most banks, insurance and property companies in the country
ended the week lower, and investment companies finished mixed.
</P>
<P>
Kuwait's Stock Exchange market's capital totaled around 14.2
billion U.S. dollars until the end of February, 1996, with
shares of the National Bank of Kuwait topping the list by
a value of 2.55 billion U.S. dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
