<HEADLINE> Tazara Improves Marketing Services </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, July 11 (Xinhua) -- The Tanzania-Zambia Railway
Authority (Tazara) is making efforts to improve its marketing
services in Zambia by moving its marketing department from the
regional headquarters in Mpika to Ndola of Copperbelt province.
</P>
<P>
The local press today quoted Tazara regional Manager for
Zambia Silas Matantilo as saying that the move was intended to
give better attention to the clients who were mostly on the
Copperbelt and Midlands.
</P>
<P>
''We just want to be near our clients on the Copperbelt and
Midlands like ZCCM (Zambia Consolidated Copper Mines) which is
our biggest client so that we give them better attention than
Mpika,'' Matantilo said.
</P>
<P>
Tazara recently has making efforts by improving services to
get itself competitive in transportation in the sub-region of
southern Africa. It installed computer information facilities for
clients and gave security ensurance of cargo and commuters on the
trains.
</P>
<P>
A snap servey carried out on the Copperbelt quoted many
exporters and commuters as saying that their apprehension about
their safety on the railway line to the port of Dar-Es-Salaam was
resolved when Tazara management assured them there was change for
the better. 
</P>
