<HEADLINE> Uganda's Population Amounts to 20 Million </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, July 11 (Xinhua) -- Uganda's population at present is
approximately 20 million, reported the local daily "the New
Vision" today.
</P>
<P>
Dan Sentamu, Director of the National Curriculum Development
Center was quoted as saying that Uganda's population has been in
recent decades growing at an average of 2.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
"This figure," he said, "is quite high as we can note from
some of the existing census figures."
</P>
<P>
For example in 1948, he said, the population of Uganda was 4.9
million while in 1991 it had grown to 16.7 million in a space of
43 years.
</P>
<P>
He lamented that the problem resulted from rapid population
growth in relation to limited resources and the poor quality of
life for the majority of people in the country.
</P>
<P>
Today, he said, most schools are crowded because of the
increasing numbers of school going children without a
corresponding increase in the number of schools.
</P>
<P>
another example related to the above mentioned issue is that
many children cannot go to school because their parents do not
have enough money to send them to, he said, adding that the
female child in the family is always the victim. 
</P>
</TEXT>
