<HEADLINE> Trolley-bus Explosion Injures Five in Downtown Moscow </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 11 (Xinhua) -- At least five people were injured
by a bomb blast in a trolley-bus in the center of Moscow Thursday
morning, said the Itar-Tass news agency here today.
</P>
<P>
The explosion occurred at about 9 a.m. (local time) when the
trolley-bus was nearing the city's Pushkin Square, which is about
one kilometer form the Kremlin.
</P>
<P>
There were few people on the bus at the time.
</P>
<P>
The driver's cabin and the front of the bus was seriously
damaged as the explosives were put under the front door, the
Interior Ministry was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the accident is still under investigation. But
some investigators said the preliminary evidence showed that it
was "a terrorist act."
</P>
<P>
The explosion occurred when the Russian troops were blocking
and bombing the Chechen leader Zelimkhan Yandarbiyev's
headquarters.
</P>
<P>
It was the second blast on Moscow's transportation system in a
month. Four people were killed in a bomb explosion on June 11 in
the Moscow subway, which the authorities called "an act of
terrorism."
</P>
<P>
The blast accidents had been obviously decreased since an
agreement was reached between the Russian government and Chechen
rebels on May 27. 
</P>
</TEXT>
