<HEADLINE> Resort Looking For More Foreign Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, July 11 (Xinhua) -- Shaoguan, a tourist resort area
in south China's Guangdong Province, is striving to come up with
at least 800 million yuan in overseas investment for
infrastructure, industry, agriculture, and tourist facilities.
</P>
<P>
According to Tang Weidong, acting mayor of the city, the money
is to be used on 80 projects, 29 of them in industry, 16 in
agriculture, eight for technology exports, 13 in transfer of
shares, and six for tourist projects.
</P>
<P>
As a tourist attraction, the city will concentrate on building
tourist facilities, using tourist resources, and building tourist
parks.
</P>
<P>
As a stop-over between coastal cities and inland areas,
Shaoguan last year attracted 3.4 times as much foreign investment
as it did in 1990, and its export volume doubled.
</P>
<P>
Domestic and foreign investment have helped improve a number of
state-owned enterprises such as a local brewery, a pharmaceutical
plant, and a gear works.
</P>
<P>
Tang said the city is planning to improve 1,900 industries by
turning them into joint ventures, or leasing and selling
them. Moreover, the city's high quality rice, bamboo, maize,
gingkos and pulpwood have also been listed as key areas for
overseas investment.  Endtiem

