<HEADLINE> Hainan's Foreign-Funded Firms Covered by Unemployment Insurance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, July 11 (Xinhua) -- More than 200 foreign-funded
enterprises on south China's Hainan Island have bought
unemployment insurance for more than 5,200 employees.
</P>
<P>
The southern province developed a detailed set of rules on
unemployment among urban residents in 1994, requiring all
enterprises and units in the city to be covered by unemployment
insurance.
</P>
<P>
A provincial official said that awareness of insurance in
foreign-funded enterprises has increased over the past two years,
and the number of enterprises and people covered by unemployment
insurance has seen a steady rise.
</P>
<P>
In the Hainan Automobile Manufacturing Plant, a large joint
venture, more than 700 employees have gotten unemployment
insurance policies that amount to more than 50,000 yuan in total.
</P>
<P>
The official pointed out, however, that some foreign-funded
enterprises, especially medium-sized and small ones, are still
outside the coverage of the unemployment insurance umbrella.
</P>
</TEXT>
