<DOCNO> XIE19960711.0154 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-07-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> APEC Ministerial Meeting on Sustainable Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 11 (Xinhua) -- Environment ministers from 18
member economies of the Asia Pacific Economic Cooperation (APEC)
began here today to discuss how to harmonize the sustainable
development of economy and the preservation of environment.
</P>
<P>
The two-day meeting will exam draft guidelines worked out by
APEC senior officials at a meeting held here on July 9-10. These
guidelines include how to promote sustainable development in mega
cities, recommendations for clean technology and clean production,
exchange of technology and information and the private-public
partnership in the sustainable development in the region.
</P>
<P>
At the opening ceremony this morning, Philippine President
Fidel Ramos called on APEC members to lay equal emphasis on the
sustainability of economic development and the protection of
environment.
</P>
<P>
"Economic growth should not come at the expense of the
environment or put it another way, that the environment should not
be sacrificed on the express train of economic growth", he said.
</P>
<P>
The president listed some elements that are threatening the
sustainable development in the region. The elements, according to
Ramos, include persistent poverty and inequity in income
distribution, high cost of social reform and persistent market
access problems for developing members.
</P>
<P>
He said that the developed members should continue to undertake
market opening measures for the products of developing members.
</P>
<P>
He also appealed to both developed and developing members to
cooperate closely in the issues being discussed.
</P>
<P>
At the end of the meeting, the delegates will try to adopt an
action plan on sustainable development and a ministerial
declaration on sustainable development at APEC.  
</P>
</TEXT>
