<DATE_TIME> 1996-07-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> APEC to Apply Environment-Friendly Standard </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 11 (Xinhua) -- The Asia Pacific Economic
Cooperation (APEC) forum will seek the use of the International
Standard Order (ISO) 14000 for a cleaner environment for
sustainable development, environment ministers of the 18 APEC
members agreed at a meeting here today.
</P>
<P>
The ISO 14000, a system grading and evaluating industries on
the basis of their environmental activities or their capability to
integrate environment protection with the production process, is
expected to be approved within the APEC by the end of this year.
</P>
<P>
According to Philippine Environment Undersecretary Delfin
Ganapin, the ISO 14000 is different from "green labeling," which
some reports said that APEC was pushing for.
</P>
<P>
He said the ISO 14000 focuses on the production system while
"green labeling" pays attention only to the product itself.
</P>
<P>
Ganapin noted that the promotion of the ISO 14000 will be to
the advantage of the developing economies of the APEC forum in the
long run.
</P>
<P>
"We promote the ISO 14000 but at the same time, parallel to it,
we promote technology transfer and transfer of expertise so that
the industries in the developing economies will be easily able to
meet the requirements of the ISO 14000," he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
