<HEADLINE> Xiaoshan Economic and Technology Zone Withstands Rough Weather </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, July 11 (Xinhua) -- Zhejiang Province's Xiaoshan
Economic and Technology Development Zone managed to withstand the
onslaught of torrential rainfall in late June.
</P>
<P>
The zone is in an area between Shanghai, Hangzhou, and Ningbo
that had a spell of heavy rainfall from the evening of June 29 to
the afternoon of July 1, with a record 195.8 millimeters of
rainfall. As of July 2, the accumulated amount was between 250
millimeters and 280 millimeters, with 14,000 hectares of land
flooded.
</P>
<P>
Fortunately, factories in the Xiaoshan Economic and Technology
Development Zone were not flooded, and pipes and roads remained
clear, so production continued as normal.
</P>
<P>
A local official attributes the good fortune to the fact that
infrastructure in the area was built to high standards.
</P>
<P>
The zone is home to businesses from Japan, the Republic of
Korea, Germany, Hong Kong, Taiwan, and Macao that have invested
700 million US dollars in the zone.  
</P>
</TEXT>
