<HEADLINE> Hubei to Develop Transportation Network </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Wuhan, July 11 (Xinhua) -- Central China's Hubei Province has
come up with a new plan to develop its transportation network, by
focusing on developing inland navigation and railways.
</P>
<P>
With the Yangtze, Hanjiang, and Qingjiang rivers running across
the province, a total of 12,000 km of waterways can be put at the
service of transportation.
</P>
<P>
The completion of a number of river ports along the Yangtze
River will also increase the province's connection with Shanghai
and other provinces.
</P>
<P>
A few major regional railways will be laid over the next 14
years, including the Wuhan-Jingmen Line (160 kms), and the
Zhicheng-Wanxian Line (420 kms).
</P>
<P>
In addition, the province will take part in construction work
on two new national railways, the Nanjing-Xi'an Line and the
Wuhan-Danjiangkou Line. 
