<HEADLINE> Shanghai Has More "Telephones Villages" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 11 (Xinhua) -- Telephones are now available in
farmers' homes in 474 suburban villages in China's largest city,
accounting for one-fifth of the city's total number of suburban
villages.
</P>
<P>
Local observers said that telephones have become one of the
farmers' favorite necessities.
</P>
<P>
In 1994. Chunshen Village in Songjiang County had 308 household
telephones for its 324 families. Chunshen installed 288 telephones
in cooperation with a nearby village.
</P>
<P>
More than 90 percent of Shanghai's total suburban villages will
have access to telephones by the year 2000, according to the
city's plan. 
