<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19960711.0174 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-07-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: 1976 Tangshan Earthquake (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Water and power supplies, telecommunications, and traffic
facilities were all destroyed by the earthquake, and production at
local factories stopped completely. Both the facilities and
instruments at local hospitals were affected.
</P>
<P>
Buildings at the Tangshan and Douhe power plants collapsed and
the equipment were destroyed. Some 30 percent of the generating
equipment at the Beijing-Tianjin-Tangshan power grid, which were
in operation or under construction, were seriously affected.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing-Shanhaiguan Railway line, which runs through
Tangshan's urban area, was severely damaged, as were feeder
railway lines.
</P>
<P>
Seven passenger and cargo trains and oil tanker trains were
derailed, and about 45 percent of the railway bridges were
severely damaged. Railway signals, telecommunications, water
supply, electric transformers, and other buildings and equipment
were also severely damaged.
</P>
<P>
Highway bridges across the Grand Canal in Hebei and over the
Luanhe River in Tangshan collapsed, halting traffic from Tangshan
to Tianjin and places outside Shanhaiguan.
</P>
<P>
Power failures caused by the earthquake stopped production work
at the Kailuan coal mines, and more than 10,000 coal cutters were
stranded in mine shafts. The mines were also flooded with leaking
water two or three days after the earthquake.
</P>
<P>
The Tangshan Iron and Steel Company's buildings, equipment,
electric power, heating power pipes, and other production
facilities were destroyed.
</P>
<P>
The dams at five large and medium-sized reservoirs within the
city were destroyed, and 240 out of 410 small reservoirs in the
city were destroyed.
</P>
<P>
A total of 500,000 mu (33,000 hectares) of arable land were
covered by blowing sand and 700,000 mu (42,000 hectares) of arable
land were flooded with salty water that came as a result.
</P>
<P>
More than 480,000 heads of domestic animals were killed by the
catastrophic earthquake. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19960711.0175 </DOCNO>
