<HEADLINE> Shanghai to Invite 300,000 Overseas Experts in 15 Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 11 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai will invite 300,000
overseas experts to the city in the next 15 years, in a move to
build the country's leading financial and industrial center into
an international economic, trade, financial and shipping area.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai will introduce yearly about 20,000 overseas senior
experts in 12 different areas, including economic development
strategy, city planning, finance, commerce and trade,
communications and telecommunications, real estate, information,
and advanced technology.
</P>
<P>
Gu Zhongxiang, an official with international personnel
exchange and cooperation at Shanghai Personnel Bureau, said that
experts on economic development strategy are familiar with
international trends in economic development and the modern market
economy, and could help Shanghai improve its share in the
economic market worldwide.
</P>
<P>
The official said most of the overseas experts will be asked to
work with Shanghai's industrial departments to develop
automobiles, communications facilities, power station equipment,
iron and steel, petrochemicals, domestic appliances, ship
building, building materials and garment manufacturing.
</P>
<P>
Gu said his city has greatly benefited from the information
offered by overseas experts about international rules and
practices, advanced technology, international competition and
personnel training.
</P>
<P>
In the past three years, Shanghai invited 17,000 overseas
experts to aid in developing its industries.  
</P>
