<HEADLINE> Mubarak Leaves for Ankara </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, July 11 (Xinhua) -- Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak
left here today for Ankara on a one-day working visit to Turkey at
the invitation of Turkish President Suleyman Demirel.
</P>
<P>
The Turkish-Israeli military agreement signed in February is
expected to be the focus of Mubarak's talks with the Turkish side
in Ankara.
</P>
<P>
Under the military agreement, Israel can use Turkey's air bases
and air space in military training.
</P>
<P>
Egypt, Syria and some other Arab states have shown special
concern over the agreement, fearing that Turkey and Israel might
forge a military alliance threatening the Arab security.
</P>
<P>
Mubarak's talks with Demirel and other senior Turkish officials
will also deal with latest developments in the Middle East,
bilateral relations and other issues of mutual concern.
</P>
<P>
Accompanying Mubarak on the visit are Foreign Minister Amr
Moussa, Information Minister Safwat el-Sherif, Chief of the Presidential
Office Zakariya Azmi and Mubarak's top political aide Osama
el-Baz. 
