<HEADLINE> Securities Accounts Top Nine Million in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 11 (Xinhua) -- The number of investors with a
trading account in the securities market in China's largest
financial center broke the nine-million mark on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that Chinese investors had 9.02 million
accounts in Shanghai by 4:00 pm Wednesday, meaning that an average
of 24,327 new accounts had been opened each trading day since May
13, when the number of securities trading accounts first went over
eight million.
</P>
<P>
Sources say that investors in Beijing, Guangdong, Zhejiang,
Hunan, and Hubei were lining up to open accounts in the Shanghai
market in the recent period, forcing some local securities
institutions to stay open at night and on the weekend.
</P>
<P>
Statistics also show that more than 75 percent of the new
accounts were opened by investors from outside Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Observers say that the new Shanghai Stock Exchange 30 Index and
some other factors are behind the recent market rally and have
boosted long-term investor confidence.
</P>
<P>
An improvement in the overall quality of companies listed on
the Shanghai exchange and a generous rate of return, as well as
other reasons, have also helped increase Shanghai securities
market's atrraction, observers say.  
</P>
</TEXT>
