<HEADLINE> More Terminology Standards For China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 11 (Xinhua) -- The State Bureau of Technological
Supervision has come up with nearly 800 standards covering more
than 100,000 technical terms, according to a working conference of
the Chinese Technical Committee for the Standardization of
Terminology.
</P>
<P>
The standardization process provides a foundation for
developing the economy, science and technology, culture, and
society and makes China a member of the International Standards
Organization.
</P>
<P>
It covers ideas and technical terms, and does something that is
indispensable to the fields of technology, information science,
culture, and language.
</P>
<P>
"It is a very important and arduous task to standardize
terminology, which covers several subjects, such as history, modern
science, technology, language, and culture," said Li Rui, deputy
head of the State Bureau of Technological Supervision.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Technical Committee for the Standardization of
Terminology was set up in 1985. The conference was intended to work
out a development plan for the Committee. 
</P>
