<HEADLINE> Home Economics Popular in Chinese Cities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, July 11 (Xinhua) -- A type of learning that used to be
offered to young women from rich families half a century ago, is
popular once again in many Chinese cities.
</P>
<P>
With the development of the economy and improving standards of
living, ordinary urban citizens have been paying more attention to
the quality of family life.
</P>
<P>
In big Chinese cities, such as Beijing, Shanghai, Nanjing,
Guangzhou and Zhengzhou, part-time training courses on family
health care, nutrition, education of children, the family, and
clothing design are on the rise.
</P>
<P>
At Jinling Women's College of Nanjing Normal University, the
Jinling Weekend Home Economics School was set up in 1994, offering
eight training courses that have been attended by over 800 people.
</P>
<P>
The university has also been authorized to train teachers of
home economics for high schools, vocational schools, and secondary
schools.
</P>
<P>
Jiangsu and Henan provinces have also established provincial
home economics associations and preparations for setting up a
national association and a number of associations at the city
level are underway.
</P>
<P>
China has held three national symposia on home economics and it
will host an international symposium in Nanjing from July 14 to 17.
</P>
<P>
Unlike the old style of home economics education, however,
today's training classes are not limited to women, and some male
students are attending the classes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
