<HEADLINE> China's Refrigerator Sales Brisk This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 11 (Xinhua) -- Demand for refrigerators in rural
areas in China has increased rapidly, which is expected to reach
12.79 million this year, 45 percent of them in rural areas, China
Light Industry News has reported.
</P>
<P>
China produced 9.3 million refrigerators in 1995 and the output
is expected to grow 20 to 30 percent this year.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that China has 188 million families in rural
areas and 105 million in urban areas with 4.03 and 62.1
refrigerators for each 100 families, respectively.
</P>
<P>
There will be about six to eight million new families each
year, pushing market demand up even more.
</P>
<P>
The paper said that rural parts of eastern China have greater
demand, and central and western parts have an annual growth rate
of only 0.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
According to the paper, almost all urban families in the
eastern part of the country have refrigerators, but that there is
still potential. 
</P>
</TEXT>
