<HEADLINE> Myanmar to Increase Port Handling Capacity </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, July 11 (Xinhua) -- Nine wharves will be built in the
next two years at the new Thilawa port near Yangon to increase
Myanmar's port handling capacity in face of the growing demand,
the official New Light of Myanmar reported today.
</P>
<P>
The Myanmar Port Authority (MPA) and Singapore's Integrated
Port Services PTE signed an agreement here Wednesday to build a
dedicated wharf -- the ninth -- at the Thilawa port, the report
said.
