signing ceremony that the wharf would consist of facilities to
handle both general cargo and bulk liquid cargo.
</P>
<P>
The port, which currently handles a combined trading volume of
about 12,000 tons of cargo a month, is expected to generate some
20,000 tons a month in the future, the minister said.
</P>
<P>
The MPA has been carrying out development projects at Thilawa
to supplement the capacity of Yangon port since June 1995 in
collaboration with foreign investors, he said.  
