<HEADLINE> Romanian population Drops in 1995 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bucharest, July 11 (Xinhua) -- Romania's population count of
22,650,000 on January 1, 1996, shows a slight decline over 1995.
</P>
<P>
The figure is 61,000 people less than the population in l994.
</P>
<P>
The birthrate in 1995 was 10.4 per 1,000, while the mortality
rate was 12 per 1,000. The major causes of death were
cardiovascular diseases and cancer.
</P>
<P>
According to Vladimir Trebici, Chairman of the Population
Committee of the Academy of Sciences of Romania, the average life
expectancy of a Romanian was less than 70, ranking as one of the
shortest in Europe.
</P>
<P>
With a working population of 11 million and a retired
population of five million, it was estimated that the ratio of
retired to workers would reduce further this year.
</P>
<P>
A report said that two million disabled people made up 8.8
percent of the national population.
</P>
<P>
In ethnic composition, Romanians comprise 89.7 percent of the
population; Hungarian, 7 percent; Gypsy, 1.8 percent; German, 0.4
percent; Ukrainian, 0.3 percent; and others, 0.8 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
