<HEADLINE> Chilean President to Meet Seven Central American Counterparts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAN JOSE, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Chilean President Eduardo Frei
will arrive here tomorrow for a two-day official visit, during
which he will meet with leaders of seven Central American
countries.
</P>
<P>
Chilean Planning Minister Luis Maira said today that Frei will
meet with his host Costa Rican President Jose Maria Figueres, the
presidents of Panama, Nicaragua, El Salvador, Honduras and
Guatemala, and the prime minister of Belize,
</P>
<P>
Frei's visit is aimed at promoting the trade between Chile and
Central American countries, which accounts for only 0.4 percent of
Chilean sales abroad.
</P>
<P>
