<HEADLINE> Maoming Becomes Two-Line Rice Research Center </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, July 11 (Xinhua) -- Maoming City in south China's
Guangdong Province has become a research center for two-line
hybrid rice.
</P>
<P>
Two-line early rice has been planted on 20,000 hectares in the
province, of which 80 percent is in Maoming.
</P>
<P>
The output for each hectare of the rice has reached at least
7,500 kilograms, 10 percent higher than that of average varieties.
</P>
<P>
Experts say that two-line rice has a larger output potential
than the three-line varieties.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the city has set up a 130-ha crop breeding base,
irrigated by low-temperature water. It is the first facility of
its kind in the country.
</P>
<P>
According to the local government, the city also plans to set
up a larger crop breeding base to provide more rice seeds for
south China's rice production.
</P>
<P>
The city has also carried out a series of research projects on
the upgrading of rice production know-how.  
</P>
