<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Population Growth Rate Drops in Peru </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Peru's population growth rate
continues dropping due to a progressive fall in birth rate, the
National Population Council said.
</P>
<P>
The council's latest figures indicated that the population
growth rate has fallen from 2.4 percent a dozen years ago to the
present 1.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
The council attributed the drop to the improvement in women's
education and their increasing participation in labor
market. Women's fertility rate dropped from 4.6 children a dozen
years ago to 3.1 children in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Peru has a population of 22.5 million, which will reach 25.662
million in four years' time if this trend continues. 
</P>
</TEXT>
