<HEADLINE> Boulmerka Suffers Defeat in Nice Athletics Meet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Algeria's world and Olympic women's
1,500 meters champion Hassiba Boulmerka suffered a big defeat in
the run-up to this month's Atlanta Games in her first major outing
of the season on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
In the event of the athletics Grand Prix meet in Nice,
Portugal's Carla Sacramento beat Boulmerka and other rivals to win
the trophy with a time of four minutes 02.64 seconds.
</P>
<P>
28-year-old Boulmerka finished seventh place in 4:05.87.
Russian Ludmilla Rogachova came second in 4:02.69 followed by
teammate Maragrita Maruseva in 4:03.01.
</P>
<P>
Torrance Zellner, who failed to make the United States
Olympic team, won the men's 400 meters hurdles with 48.24 seconds
followed by Zambian Samuel Matete in 48.27 and American Eric
Thomas in 48.55.
</P>
<P>
In the women's 800 meters, Cuban world champion Ana Fidelia
Quirot clocked her best time of 1:59.21 this year and won the
race.
</P>
<P>
Sweden's Ludmila Engquist, formerly russian Narozhilenko,
destroyed her rivals to win the women's 100-meter hurdles in 12.67
seconds.
</P>
<P>
The 3,000-meter steeplechase top three places went to keyans
with Joseph Ketter winning the title in 8 minutes 08.47.
</P>
<P>
In the hammer, Hungary's Balazs Kiss produced the best
performance in the world this year with a throw of 81.76 meters.
</P>
<P>
Charles Austin of the United States snatched the men's high
jump champion with 2.34 meters while Yugoslavian Dragutin Topic
finished second with 2.32 meters.
</P>
<P>
In the men's 100 meters race, canada's world champion Donovam
Nailey beat Britain's Olympic champion Lindford Christie to the
second place. Both Bailey and Christie were timed in 10.17
seconds. 
