<HEADLINE> Cuban National Student Games Inaugurated </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, July 10 (Xinhua) -- The 32nd Cuban National Student
Sports Games were inaugurated today with the participation of more
than 5000 student including 380 from different Latin American
countries.
</P>
<P>
The competitions will be held in Havana and another 9 sites on
the island.
</P>
<P>
The main inaugural ceremony was held in the Polivalente Ramon
Fonst Hall in Havana where several of the competitions in 29
sports began.
</P>
<P>
The games feature swimming, diving, synchronized swimming,
tennis, gymnastics, cycling, shooting, sailing, chess, baseball,
soccer, karate, basketball, wrestling, field hockey and Taekwondo.
</P>
<P>
The foreign student participants are from Mexico, Peru,
Puerto Rico, the Dominican Republic, Honduras, Argentina and
Venezuela. 
</P>
