<HEADLINE> Soeharto's Medical Checkup Nearly Over </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAKARTA, July 11 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian president Soeharto
Wednesday almost completed his health checkup in Germany with all
the result so far described as favorable, the official Antara News
Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
Research and Technology Minister BJ. Habibie who accompanied
the president for a medical checkup in Bad Oeynhausen, a small
town in Germany, said that tests on the president's blood, heart,
liver, gall and spleen all turned out negative.
</P>
<P>
The president was scheduled to undergo ear, nose and throat
tests on Thursday, the minister was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Habibie said catether and angiographic tests showed all of the
president's organs were functioning well.
</P>
<P>
"A small unmovable 'stone' was found in the kidney but the
problem has been overcome," he said, adding that "we know
President Soeharto experienced it before."
</P>
<P>
He said President Soeharto remained scheduled to return home on
Sunday and start work on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The president left here last Sunday. He is accompanied on the
trip by several of his children and grandchildren and some others.
</P>
<P>
</P>
