<DOCNO> XIE19960711.0259 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-07-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rapid Growth in Hubei's Township Enterprises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, July 11 (Xinhua) -- Central China's Hubei Province has
enjoyed a 47.35 percent increase in output of its township
enterprises, amounting to 63.7 billion yuan in the first five
months of the year.
</P>
<P>
The province will find ways, over the next five years, of
spurring growth in the enterprises, which play a key role in
farmers' incomes.
</P>
<P>
Total output value of township enterprises in the province is
expected to hit 670 billion yuan during the 1996-2000 period,
according to provincial authorities.
</P>
<P>
The methods to be taken include increasing bank lending,
concentrating funds in high-tech projects, increasing exportable
products, supporting firms that have a good track record, and
encouraging enterprise groups.
</P>
<P>
Those enterprises processing agricultural by-products will get
government support for both project approval and for funding,
while those offering services for agricultural production will be
exempt from income tax.
</P>
<P>
The province is one of China's major automobile producers, and
township industries there have grown rapidly in the 1990s, and had
an output value of 252 billion yuan from 1991 to 1995.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
