<HEADLINE> Lazarenko Named Ukraine's New PM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Ukraine's parliament today named
Pavlo Lazarenko new prime minister, paving the way for him to form
a new Cabinet.
</P>
<P>
A total of 344 lawmakers voted for, and 22 against, Lazarenko,
a result hailed as an "extremely responsible decision" by
Parliament speaker Oleksandr Moroz.
</P>
<P>
Lazarenko and the government resigned last week after the
adoption of a new constitution, which calls for naming a new
Cabinet. Lazarenko, head of Soviet-time farm, now has three
months to form his cabinet.
</P>
<P>
President Leonid Danilovich Kuchma appointed him in May after
firing Premier Yevhen Marchuk for mishandling economic reforms
together with several other top officials, including Defense
Minister Valery Shmarov. 
</P>
