<HEADLINE> Labor Party Criticizes Netanyahu For Hardline </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, July 10 (Xinhua) -- In its reaction to Prime
Minister Benjamin Netanyahu's hardline remarks in Washington, the
opposition Labor Party has charged that he has in fact closed
peace options.
</P>
<P>
Moshe Shahal, Member of Knesset (MK) and former minister of
public security, said, "what Mr. Netanyahu did in Washington has
proved that he is more connected with his slogans before
elections than to be a prime minister trying to find a way to
solve problems."
</P>
<P>
He noted that Netanyahu has come into what he called "a
collision course" with the Arab countries.
</P>
<P>
