elections, no doubt, Clinton, if elected, will put pressure on
Israel and Mr. Netanyahu to follow agreements and implement every
word of the agreements that have been signed. And let's not forget
that the U.S. has signed the agreements as a partner."
</P>
<P>
"We don't like American pressure here and we insist in
Israeli independence and that its government should take any
decisions needed here," he said. "But let's not forget the
U.S. is an international superpower. It cannot look at the
situation here to allow it to collapse, or withdraw in the
peace process, keeping silence."
</P>
<P>
He said that Israel gets three billion a year of foreign aid
for the U.S.. "There is no doubt in a way that something is at
stake for whom to give the aid," he added. 
</P>
