<HEADLINE> Popularity Rates of Chirac, Juppe Drops Slightly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 10 (Xinhua) -- The popularity rates of French
president Jacques Chirac and prime minister Alain Juppe in June
dropped by one percentage points and two percentage points as are
compared with those of May.
</P>
<P>
The Louis Harris/Valeurs Actuelles polling group said today
that 44 percent of French people evaluate as "good" the
performance of Chirac as "President of the Republic", and 50
percent judge his performance as "bad", while six percent
refrain from making a judgment, according to a latest polling by
the group.
</P>
<P>
Thirty-four percent of the people reached by the polling said
Juppe's performance as prime minister is "good", and 60 percent
regard his performance as "bad".
</P>
<P>
The polling was made through telephone calls on July 5-6 that
reached 1,001 people who are 18 years old and above.
</P>
<P>
The margin of error is not mentioned. 
</P>
</TEXT>
