<HEADLINE> Airbus Has Half of World's Plane Transactions This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 10 (Xinhua) -- The Airbus Industry European
Consortium has received 143 new orders amounting to 11.1 billion
U.S. dollars in the first three months this year, Airbus
headquarters in Toulouse, southern France, announced today.
</P>
<P>
The orders already go beyond in amount all those received by
the consortium in 1995, and its net sale in the first three months
of 1996 amounted to 136 planes, which represents 48 percent of the
global plane transactions of the period, said Airbus.
</P>
<P>
The orders, which came from 15 clients worldwide, gave Airbus
37 percent of global market selling planes with more than 100
seats. 
</P>
</TEXT>
