<HEADLINE> Greece, Chile Sign Cooperation Agreements </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Greek Foreign Minister Theodoros
Pangalos today signed two economic and commercial agreements with
his Chilean counterpart, Jose Miguel Insulza who began an official
two-day visit here.
</P>
<P>
After the signing, both ministers underlined the excellent
bilateral relations between the two countries, the traditional
friendship between the two peoples and the steady cooperation both
at the united nations and within the framework of the European
Union's cooperation with the countries of Latin America.
</P>
<P>
Pangalos said Chile was playing a leading role in Latin
America, was building a stable democracy and had an exceptional
economic performance, particularly in recent years.
</P>
<P>
Insulza thanked Pangalos for Greece's contribution to the
signing of a Chilean-EU cooperation agreement. He said he had
discussed with Pangalos the prospects for future relations between
the countries of Latin America and Europe.
</P>
<P>
Noting the excellent level of relations between the two
countries, Insulza said they had been further improved in the last
six years following the reciprocal establishment of embassies.
</P>
<P>
He described as "very important" the agreements signed today,
stressing that Greek-Chilean commercial relations were "good".
</P>
<P>
Apart from the two agreements signed today, Insulza said,
Greece and Chile would soon be discussing closer cooperation in
the sector of shipping. 
</P>
</TEXT>
