<HEADLINE> Heat Wave Over in Balkans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, July 10 (Xinhua) -- A heat wave that claimed at
least 16 lives in the Balkans was driven out today by clouds and
cold winds, which brought in showers in the region.
</P>
<P>
The cold front from the Baltic Sea brought relief to Romania,
the southern part of which registered the highest temperatures in
11 years in the past few days, and to Bulgaria, Serbia and Greece.
</P>
<P>
As the front advances, temperatures in this Romanian capital
city dropped to 18 degrees Celsius today, as compared to 40
degrees on Monday and 35 degrees on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
According to forensic and medical experts, in Romania alone, 16
people died of strokes and heart failure caused by the unusually
searing heat and hundreds more were sickened. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
