<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UK Commercial Vehicle Sales Stagnate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Growth in the commercial vehicle
market in Britain came to a virtual halt in the first half of this
year, leaving manufacturers of heavy truck worried about their
prospects for 1996 as a whole, according to the Society of Motor
Manufacturers and Traders (SMMT).
</P>
<P>
Figures from the SMMT show that three of the four biggest
market sectors, panel vans, trucks over 3.5 tons and heavy
trucks over 15 tons, fell in June, leaving total new commercial
vehicle sales for the first half of this year just 0.9 percent
higher than a year ago, at 130,907 units.
</P>
<P>
Only an upsurge in sales of small vans last month prevented the
total market in the first half of this year slipping below last
year's level.
</P>
<P>
Most badly-hit last month was the heavy trucks sector, where
sales declined to 2,215 from the previous June's 2,642. This left
the sector more than nine percent down for the year's first six
months.
</P>
<P>
Light van sales in June rose to 5,842 from 4,961 the previous
June; those of panel vans fell to 8,355 from 8,528 and those of
trucks over 3.5 tonnes to 4,050 from 4,521.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19960711.0309 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-07-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Japan, U.S. Try to Balance Bilateral Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Japan and the United States will
make further efforts to rectify the bilateral trade imbalance
heavily in Japan's favor, according to a joint statement reached
by the two countries here today.
</P>
<P>
The bilateral trade issues should be resolved on the private
level before they become politicized, said the statement, which
was adopted after three days of discussions.
</P>
<P>
It also said that it is necessary for both sides to continue
efforts to maintain the downward trend in Japan's trade surplus
with the United States.
</P>
<P>
The business leaders of the two countries also discussed issues
including Asian markets and China's entry to the World Trade
Organization. 
</P>
