<HEADLINE> 14 Zimbabweans Dead, 21 Injured in Bus Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Fourteen Zimbabweans died
instantly on Tuesday morning when a Zimbabwe United Passenger
Company (ZUPCO) bus in which they were travelling rammed into a
stationary lorry along the Chimanimani-Harare road.
</P>
<P>
The Zimbabwe National News Agency reported today that another
21 passengers received multiple injuries and three of them were
reported to be in a critical condition.
</P>
<P>
The accident, which occurred near Cashel Valley, comes barely
three months after the Chipinge lorry disaster in which 29 casual
workers died when two lorries collided in the Middle Sabi, in the
same Manicaland province.
</P>
<P>
Police provincial public relations and liaison officer Dorothy
Muchenga said that eight men died on the spot together with six
females. 
</P>
