<HEADLINE> Nigeria Starts Nationwide Bird Survey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, July 10 (Xinhua) -- The Nigerian Conservation
Foundation is embarking on a nationwide survey aimed at
identifying and updating the spatial and temporal distribution of
birds in the country.
</P>
<P>
The project, known as the bird areas survey and supported by
the Royal Society for the Protection of Birds, will pay
particular attention to southwestern states where the occurrence
of "as yet undescribed species is reported".
</P>
<P>
According to the foundation, birds are generally seen as
significant indicators of the health of their environment, and
the project is coming at a time when global bird population is
believed to be declining. 
