<HEADLINE> German Tourist Shot to Death in Florida </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 10 (Xinhua) -- A German tourist was found
murdered in the street in Fort Myers, Florida, and the car he was
driving was missing.
</P>
<P>
The body of the tourist, Gerd-Ulrich Ladwig, was Tuesday found
lying in the street, riddled with bullets, the Associated Press
said.
</P>
<P>
Ladwig, who was from the northern German city of Hannover, had
been shot several times and the silver Mercedes he was driving was
missing, the sheriff's office was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
His wife said that she last saw him shortly before midnight
Monday when he told her he was having trouble sleeping and was
going to a downtown restaurant for a drink. But the restaurant
owner did not see him.
</P>
<P>
Ladwig was the third tourist killed in Florida this year. In
March, a Canadian young man was shot to death during a botched
robbery while talking to his mother on a pay phone in Daytona
Beach. In February, a Dutch woman was murdered after she and her
husband stopped to ask for directions in the Miami area, according
to the report.
</P>
<P>
The Florida tourism industry has been trying for three years to
recover from image problems following murders of 10 foreign
tourists within 13 months, the report said. 
</P>
