<HEADLINE> Netanyahu Urges Isolation of Iran, Iraq </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin
Netanyahu pleased the U.S. Congress today by fiercely attacking
Iran and Iraq, calling them as "despotic regimes."
</P>
<P>
He strongly backed the U.S. initiative to isolate the two
states and slammed European and Asian countries for maintaining
relations with them.
</P>
<P>
Speaking in the U.S. Congress on his second day of the America
tour, the hardline Likud leader said that if the two neighboring
states acquired nuclear weapons, there could be "catastrophic
consequences" for the world.
</P>
<P>
He called on the United States to lead an international effort
to isolate the two states and bragged that only the United States
and Israel have been at the forefront of the efforts to prevent
their acquisition of nuclear weapons.
</P>
<P>
He lectured the European and Asian countries not to be
short-sighted for some material gain.
</P>
<P>
"Europe and the countries of Asia must be made to understand
that it is folly... to pursue short-term material gain while
creating a long-term existential danger for all of us," he said.
</P>
<P>
He won a long ovation in the Congress as the House of
Representatives had approved legislation that would impose
stringent new sanctions on Iran, and the Senate is expected to
consider the measure later this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
