<HEADLINE> Angola's Ruling Party to Hold National Congress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, July 10 (Xinhua) -- The People's Liberation Movement
of Angola will hold a national congress in October, Secretary for
Political Affairs of the ruling party Norberto Dos Santos
announced here today.
</P>
<P>
Dos Santos told reporters that at the congress "intensive"
discussions will be held on the Angolan peace process, its social
and economic situation and the party's internal life.
</P>
<P>
He added that the party will also discuss how to face new
challenges of the multi-party system and how to carry out
deepgoing social and economic reforms.
</P>
<P>
He said 750 people will be present at the congress. The
resolutions to be passed by the congress are expected to have a
great impact on Angola's political stability and economic
recovery and development. 
</P>
</TEXT>
