<HEADLINE> Sino-Zimbabwean Friendly Relations Praised </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Acting Zimbabwe President Simon
Muzenda today spoke highly of the traditional friendship between
Zimbabwe and China and urged for better bilateral cooperation.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks in a meeting with a visiting Chinese
delegation led by Governor of Yunnan Province He Zhiqiang here
this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Muzenda said China extended valuable support to Zimbabwe in
its struggle for independence and it continued to assist Zimbabwe
in economic development after its independence.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his thanks for China's assistance to his country.
</P>
<P>
He said he found many great changes had taken place in China
in his visits to that country.
</P>
<P>
He said he wants to learn from China's economic reforms,
especially those in the agricultural sector, during his next
visit to China.
</P>
<P>
He Zhiqiang said, ''Zimbabwe's experience in tobacco
production, distribution and marketing, research and new
technique popularization merits our learning.'' In the past days,
He visited some tobacco farms, tobacco auction floors and tobacco
research institutes.
</P>
<P>
He said there are broad prospects for bilateral cooperatrion
in the tobacco industry.
</P>
<P>
The Yunnan delegation arrived in Zimbabwe on Monday and will
leave here for home Friday. enditem

